<en-note><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Installing the Java JDK8</span> ( Open JDK8)</div><div>=&gt; cd /usr/ports/java/openjdk8</div><div>=&gt; export BATCH=1 </div><div>=&gt; sudo make -DBATCH install clean</div><div><font color="#929292">( I didn’t have to these for Java 8 )</font></div><div><font color="#929292">Edit the &quot;/etc/fstab&quot; and add the lines:</font></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"><font color="#929292">fdesc /dev/fd fdescfs rw 0 0</font></span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"><font color="#929292">proc /proc procfs rw 0 0</font></span></div><div><font color="#929292">=&gt; sudo mount -a</font></div><div><br/></div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">sudo ln -s</span> /usr/local/openjdk8  /usr/local/java</div><div><br/></div><div>ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">JAVA_HOME</span> = /usr/local/openjdk8</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">JAVAC</span> = ${JAVA_HOME}/bin/javac</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">JAVA</span> = ${JAVA_HOME}/bin/java</div><div>( no space between !!!)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>
